&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor daily production and operational status of our solar and battery energy storage systems using Nexamp monitoring tools and standard operation procedures (SOPs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, acknowledge, analyze, and prioritize alarms and alerts, ensuring timely response to critical events and appropriate escalation to field service, engineering, and other stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform basic remote troubleshooting and control actions within defined SOPs, including independently monitoring and operating assets, and document actions taken in the monitoring and fleet management systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly and professionally with customers, utilities, equipment manufacturers, field technicians, and internal Nexamp teams via phone, email, and ticketing/monitoring platforms to coordinate safe and efficient issue resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and triage the operations email inbox, including alarms, site notifications, and vendor communications, routing and escalating messages based on SOPs and operational priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate logs and records of outages, events, and resolutions in Nexamp’s monitoring and fleet management tools to support reporting, root cause analysis, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously seek to optimize monitoring practices, alarm configurations, and SOPs in collaboration with team members to enhance safety, responsiveness, and asset performance.&lt;/li&gt;
